# Symfony Accelerator

This project ships a skill-based workflow for Symfony layered architecture:

```text
Controller -> Service -> Repository
```

## Command -> Agent -> Skill

- **Commands** (`.cursor/commands/*.md`) are `/slash` entry points; invoke with `/name` and pass context as `$ARGUMENTS`.
- **Agents** (`.cursor/agents/*.md`) run one skill in an isolated context, then stop.
- **Skills** (`.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`) contain the actual workflow.

Execute only the selected skill, then stop. Do not auto-chain. Always end with a Context Summary and Next Steps.

## Typical Flow

`requirements-analyst` -> `researcher` -> `brainstorm` -> `council` -> `architect` -> `database-designer` -> `api-designer` -> `writing-plans` -> `architecture-implementer` -> `coder` / `coder-frontend` -> `test-generator` -> `code-reviewer` / `security-reviewer` -> `verify` -> `finishing-branch` / `release`

Support skills: `dependency-manager`, `refactorer`, `performance-optimization`, `systematic-debugger`, `documentation-generator`, `review-pr`, `reflect`.

## Sources Of Truth

Enforcement (`.cursor/hooks`) > Policy (`AGENTS.md`) > Architecture (`specs/`) > Skills (`.cursor/skills/`) > Examples > Docs. See `.cursor/DOD.md`, `.cursor/GOLDEN-PRINCIPLES.md`, and `examples/symfony-clean-code-patterns.md`.
